  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">F.a: Promoting and advocating for the rights of persons with disabilities through raising awareness at grass roots</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is for the advocacy in the fundamental rights and opportunities of PWDs through participation, involvement and provision of information.  The main activities are one day orientation meeting with 25 community leaders and stakeholders, 5 days res
idential training workshop on advocacy and human rights for 25 members of the organisation, awareness campaigns and advocacy in 10 areas of the district, establishment of disability clubs, exchange visits for 15 members to a disability organisation in the 
region as well as distribution of information, education and communication materials (IEC).</narrative>
  </description>
